{"lemma":"سَعْيُ","slug":"سَعْيُ","root":"س.ع.#","root_slug":"س-ع-_","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ع-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"سَعْي","root":"سعي","pos":"N","occurrence_count":10},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n19861","n19866"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%8A%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of سَعَى (saʕā) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"endeavor, effort, exertion, zeal"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cooperation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"career, course"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/saʕj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n19861","headword_ar":"سَعَى","root":"sEw and sEY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasoEaY","text_ar":"يَسْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEoYN","text_ar":"سَعْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, &c.) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoEFY","text_ar":"مَسْعًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with general analogy],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He walked, went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Er-Rághib, Mgh, TA:) this, accord. to Er-Rághib, is the primary signification: and hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aEoYu bayona AlS~afaA waAlmarowapi","text_ar":"السَّعْىُ بَيْنَ الصَّفَا وَالمَرْوَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The tripping to and fro between Es-Safà and ElMarweh"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY fiY ma$oyihi","text_ar":"سَعَى فِى مَشْيِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He tripped along,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he trudged along, in his walking"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Msb:) [or]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aEoYu","text_ar":"السَّعْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the going along with vigorousness, and with lightness, activity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 665.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a man, S)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (IAar, S, K, TA;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY","text_ar":"جَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": by the former of which is meant ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a pace below what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ad~u","text_ar":"الشَّدُّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and above what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alma$oYu","text_ar":"المَشْىُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IAar, TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaSada","text_ar":"قَصَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He repaired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"betook himself"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) The saying, in the Kur [lxii. 9],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^osoEawoA A_ilaY *ikori A@oll~`hi","text_ar":"فَاْسْعَوْا اـِلَى ذِكْرِ ا@ْللّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAqoSiduwA","text_ar":"فَاقْصِدُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Then repair ye to prayer to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"then go ye"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^omoDuwA","text_ar":"فَاْمْضُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to prayer"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to God"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Jel:) and Ibn-Mes'ood read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faA^omoDuwA","text_ar":"فَاْمْضُوا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY A_ilaY AlS~alaApi","text_ar":"سَعَى اـِلَى الصَّلَاةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went to prayer, in any manner"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"quickly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Msb.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He was active,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"busy and bustling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in procuring the means of subsistence: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he strove, laboured,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exerted himself; employed himself vigorously, strenuously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with energy;"},{"kind":"text","text":"in any affair, whether good or evil; but mostly used in relation to what is praiseworthy, or praised: (Er-Rághib, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he occupied himself according to his own judgment"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discretion"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"free will,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in any work, or deed: (Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he worked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, TA,) any work, or deed, good or evil: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gained."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa yasoEaY EalaY qawomihi","text_ar":"هُوَ يَسْعَى عَلَى قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He manages, conducts, orders, regulates,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superintends, the affairs of his people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 771, Msb. *) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY lahumo","text_ar":"سَعَى لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohimo","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He worked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrought, and earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gained, for them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almaro'u","text_ar":"المَرْءُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasoEaY ligaArayohi","text_ar":"يَسْعَى لِغَارَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a prove., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The man earns for his belly and his pudendum."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY AlmukaAtibu fiY Eitoqi raqabatihi","text_ar":"سَعَى المُكَاتِبُ فِى عِتْقِ رَقَبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY faki raqabatihi","text_ar":"فِى فَكِ رَقَبَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The slave who had made a contract with his master to pay him a certain sum for his emancipation"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laboured to earn the means of releasing himself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the inf. n. of the verb thus used is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEaAyapN","text_ar":"سعَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, Msb:) and this term is employed when a slave emancipated in part, and in part retained in slavery, labours and earns for the completion of his release. (IAth, TA.) The saying, in the Kur [liii. 40],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa liloA_inosaAni A_il~aA maA","text_ar":"لَيْسَ لِلْاـِنْسَانِ اـِلَّا مَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY","text_ar":"سَعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"There is nothing"},{"kind":"text","text":"imputable"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the man"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"but what he hath wrought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"done."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"falam~aA balaga maEahu A^ols~aEoYa","text_ar":"فَلَمَّا بَلَغَ مَعَهُ اْلسَّعْىَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the same [xxxvii. 100], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And when he attained to working with him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and when he was able to assist him in his working."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He superintended, managed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conducted, in his own person, the collection of the poor-rates;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went to exact them, and received them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and the inf. n. in this case also is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siEaAyapN","text_ar":"سِعَايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY EalaY AlS~adaqapi","text_ar":"سَعَى عَلَى الصَّدَقَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasoEaY","text_ar":"يَسْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEoYN","text_ar":"سَعْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he officiated in the exacting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"receiving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"collecting, of the poor-rate."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * Msb.) [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY","text_ar":"سَعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is trans. without a prep. as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exacted"},{"kind":"text","text":"the poor-rate:] a poet says, (namely, 'Amr Ibn-'Addà, TA,)"},{"kind":"quote","text":"saEaY EiqaAlFA falamo yatoruko lanaA sabadFA\n                      \n                     \n                        fakayofa lawo qado saEaY EamorNw EiqaAlayoni"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He exacted the poor-rate of a year, and left not to us camels' fur,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats' hair: then how"},{"kind":"text","text":"would be the case"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"if 'Amr had exacted the poor-rate of two years?"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEayotu fiY A^amori fulaAnK","text_ar":"سَعَيْتُ فِى اَمْرِ فُلَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said when one rectifies, redresses, or reforms, the affair of such a one, or mars, vitiates, or perverts it, by his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEoY","text_ar":"سَعْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or striving, or labouring; and may be rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I strove,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"laboured, in respect of the affair of such a one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to rectify, redress,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reform, it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to mar, vitiate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pervert, it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waA@l~a*iyna saEawoA fiY A=yaAtinaA","text_ar":"وَا@لَّذِينَ سَعَوْا فِى ا=يَاتِنَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur xxii. 50 [and xxxiv. 5], means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And they who strive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour, in respect of our signs, to mar,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vitiate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pervert, their meaning, by impugning their character;"},{"kind":"text","text":"seeing that they called them enchantment, and poetry, and tales, or legends, or fictions: (Ksh in xxii. 50:) or these words of the Kur mean"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and they who strive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour, to falsify,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nullify, our signs;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. the Kur-án. (Jel.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY bayonahumo","text_ar":"سَعَى بَيْنَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He created,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited, disorder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discord, between them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among them; made,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, mischief between them,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among them;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saA^aA","text_ar":"سَاَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is app., in this case, a dial. var. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY","text_ar":"سَعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sA^w","text_ar":"ساو"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY bayona Aln~aAsi biAln~amaAy^imi","text_ar":"سَعَى بَيْنَ النَّاسِ بِالنَّمَايِمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He created,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"excited, disorder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among the people by calumnies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slanders:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or it may be well rendered"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he busied himself among the people with propagating calumnies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slanders"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S and O in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akl","text_ar":"اكل"},{"kind":"text","text":"; &c.) ―         -b8-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEaY","text_ar":"سَعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He calumniated him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slandered him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY AlwaAliY","text_ar":"اـِلَى الوَالِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the ruler,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"magistrate"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, Msb, K;) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEiAyapN","text_ar":"سَعِايَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEato","text_ar":"سَعَتْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", said of a female slave, (K, TA,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tasoEaY","text_ar":"تَسْعَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEoYN","text_ar":"سَعْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"She committed fornication,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prostituted herself."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) [See also 3.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAEaAniY fulaAnN fasaEayotuhu","text_ar":"سَاعَانِى فُلَانٌ فَسَعَيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 3."}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","Jel","S","K"]},{"entry_id":"n19866","headword_ar":"سَعْىٌ","root":"sEw and sEY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1 [in most of its senses]. (S, Msb, K, &c.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEoyapu","text_ar":"سَعْيَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}